      "role": "user",
      "content": "but is it really \"successful\" if it can't do anything about things like the war in Syria or the situation in Ukraine? some people say the whole structure is actually just broken and serves the interests of a few powerful countries rather than actually maintaining peace. do historians see those as just growing pains or is the institution itself fundamentally flawed?",
