    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean, if it's fundamentally incapable of doing its main job because of those vetoes, why do historians still treat it as a legitimate authority? it feels like we're just pretending it works when it's basically just a club for the winners of WWII to protect their own interests. isn't it more accurate to say its legitimacy is basically gone?",
